67. Pray (if you are religious)

90. Road trips.
91. Spontaneous adventures.
92. The feeling of sand beneath your toes.

Hoje o ator Paul Walker (1973-2013) e seu amigo piloto Roger Rodas (1975-2013) sofria um acidente fatal que custou as suas vidas no Valencia, um bairro de Santa Clarita, Califórnia! Este foi o dia mais triste para nós fãs da franquia Velozes & Furiosos (Fast & Furious), fiquei muito abalado com a notícia da morte do Paul já que sou fã da franquia tem quase duas décadas que eu acompanho (não me lembro o que estava fazendo no momento que foi anunciado a sua morte e de seu amigo)! Estava gravando o filme Velozes & Furiosos 7 já que tinha gravado a metade do filme e para finalizar o que estava faltando os seus irmãos foram dublê de corpo e dois anos depois foi lançado o filme que iria se tornar mais lucrativo da franquia (não me lembro se fui ver na primeira semana) e fui ver seu último filme e já sabia que iria sair arrasado quando acabou, e quando começou a homenagem para ele comecei a chorar muito (nunca tinha chorado assim pelo um artista) e ele é o único que me aconteceu vendo seus melhores momentos da franquia mais amado por mim, finalmente acabei sair da sala do cinema e a minha mãe me viu chorando muito! Todos os filmes lançados posteriores foram homenageado para ele já que não tem como lembrar do Brian O'Conner e tem homenagear mesmo! Sempre revejo a franquia para matar a saudades que sinto por você e outros filmes que ainda não vi!

Every time I listen to this song, I think about my now graduated friends that left me behind after 3 years of me knowing them.

Here's the story:

It all started when me and the friend I now have on discord met each other when I was a freshman in highschool, in the first year, me, him and another friend of his played Yu-Gi-Oh Nexus together. After that year, we had to same class again, but this time, he and more of his friends played SSBU (Super Smash Bros Ultimate for those who don't know) together, I was intrigued by their skill and I joined them, from what I distinctively remember, a few weeks later. That's when the friend I have on discord become my SSBU tag team partner, I played Simon, he played Richtor, I played Lucina, he played Marth, HECK, we've done double Ganondorf and so much more. That is when I truly felt a connection between us. In my junior and his senior year, which was last year, we still played SSBU, and I never thought I would build a new connection between me, him and his friends. When they had to leave 2 weeks before graduation during our yearly senior walkout, I was crying tears of emotion, knowing they were gonna be gone when they graduated 2 weeks from that day. 2 weeks later, I went to their graduation to help National Honors Society with passing out programs, not only that, I wanted to support my friends all the way through the program, best of all, they DID NOT know I was there. At the end, I never had a final encounter with those friends to say a final farewell..... but there was something coming from a friend I had never had before...... The friend on discord sent me this exact message, "Thank you for everything! You're an amazing friend!" That is where I CRIED tears of emotion, because I have never had a friend that was THAT supportive to me, EVER. That was the last I have heard from him or the others......That is how those 3 years (2020-2023) were some of the best years of my highschool life.😭

I still think about them to this day 🥺



UPDATE AFTER SUMMER 2023: I am doing well....but I am still depressed they are gone.....But they will always be in my heart.....forever 😭

This song always makes me cry, especially the ending scene when Vin Diesel and Paul Walker go their separate ways. I can’t imagine how hard it must have been for the cast and crew to film that scene, knowing that Paul was gone. They were like a family, and they lost one of their own. This song marks for me the weird, sad, contradictory but for some odd reason still comforting time of my life. At May 2015, as I myself was turning 14, my dad passed away without any symptoms in advance, of coronary artery disease, just a day before turning 50. In hindsight he couldn’t have had better way to go. He died at last day of any sort of youth and hence stays forever ”young”, which I also find somewhat poetic. He obviously finished a bit early but definitely in the way he’d always wanted doing his work he loved, far away from the eyes of us who’d get traumatized for the rest of our lives. 

The odd part is, and it may be a false memory but I reckon hearing this song somewhere a couple of days before, and I saw the movie just three weeks before the day about to change the very structure of my life. This song brings me contradictory vibe of warmth of the following summer of 2015 but reminds also about cathartic irreplaceability of long-gone beloved family member. ❤

My childhood friend passed away yesterday. Unfortunately, his cancer had returned... I don't know how to describe it... Losing one of my childhood friends is very sad... When I got the news, I thought it was a prank, but I soon realized it wasn't... That's when my heart broke into pieces...

He'll always be like an older brother to me... Our memories will remain alive in my heart, memories of shared laughter, unforgettable adventures, and moments that shaped our friendship. It's hard to accept the reality of his absence, but I promise to honor his memory by remembering our good times together.

Every time I look back, I will remember his warm presence and impact on my life. The longing will be eternal, as will the gratitude for having had him as a friend.
 
That's why I listen to this song to keep our memories.
